programme.title: My Transgender Summer Camp
programme.desc: Features exclusive access to an American camp for transgender adolescents and their parents. The film My Transgender Summer Camp explores the difficult next steps faced by a group of ordinary girls who were born boys. As well as summer fun, they must face huge dilemmas including whether or not to begin hormone blockers to halt male puberty.

programme.title: Kumu Hina
programme.desc: Imagine a world where a little boy can grow up to be the woman of his dreams, and a young girl can rise to become a leader among men. Welcome to Kumu Hina's Hawai'i. Kumu Hina tells the inspiring story of Hina Wong-Kalu, a transgender native Hawaiian teacher, or kumu, who brings to life Hawai'i's traditional embrace of mahu - those who embody both male and female spirit. Produced by Emmy-winning directors Dean Hamer and Joe Wilson in association with ITVS and Pacifc Islanders in Communications, the film traces Hina's evolution from Collin Wong, a timid high school boy, to her present position as a married woman and cultural director of a school in one of Honolulu's grittier neighborhoods. When Ho'onani, a charismatic 6th grade girl, asks to join the school's all-male hula troupe, Kumu Hina gives her the opportunity to express her inner male spirit. As teacher and student prepare for a climactic end-of-year public performance, they meet many obstacles, but hold fast to the idea that being true to oneself matters most.

programme.title: Greetings From Fire Island

programme.title: Gay USA
programme.desc: In June 1977, Director Arthur J. Bressan, Jr. mobilized camera crews across the country to document National Gay Freedom Day marches. Gay USA conveys the passion, anger, and defiant optimism of a community under attack, and illustrates the triumphant power of love and pride. Beautifully restored in 2K by the UCLA Film & Television Archive in collaboration with Frameline and Outfest.

programme.title: Political Animals
programme.desc: Political Animals celebrates the legendary civil rights victories of four trailblazing California state politicians: Carole Migden, Sheila Keuhl, Jackie Goldberg, and Christine Kehoe. Fierce and unrelenting, these courageous women toppled a partisan majority and emerged victors to pass historic legislation for social justice and LGBT+ equality. It was a hard fight - filled with vehemently heated debates and hateful insults hurled by opponents. Today, the message behind Political Animals is more important than ever as the current political theatre unfurls around the globe. These inspiring biographies further reveal the critical importance for public resistance at the local level to pressure lawmakers to enact difficult change. Political Animals is a clear call to action for a new era of greater democratic participation. We invite you to follow in the footsteps of these historic leaders and become the next pioneering political animal!

programme.title: The World Poker Tour Season 11 Episode 4
programme.desc: The Legends of Poker is under way and tensions are racking up early in this historic second decade of the World Poker Tour. In his very first WPT event the lone amateur on the felt, Josh Hale, has surmounted a staggering chip-lead but with five talented pros each as eager for the victory, the illustrious Champions Cup could find itself in anyone’s hands. Kimberly Lansing anchors the action while Mike Sexton and Vince Van Patten bring you the energetic play by play from the tournament that is just too good to miss.

programme.title: The World Poker Tour Season 11 Episode 5
programme.desc: There are even more twists and turns to be had at the Bicycle Casino where the players’ chip counts rise and fall with dramatic consequences. So far only one player has been eliminated and so five remain to fight for the chance to have their name engraved on the prestigious WPT Champion’s Cup. Off the felt anchor Kimberly Lansing takes a look at previous and current player of the year contenders while poker Hall of Famer Mike Sexton and Hollywood’s own Vince Van Patten guide us though the play to determine the WPT “legend of poker”.

programme.title: The World Poker Tour Season 11 Episode 6
programme.desc: The Legends of Poker is coming to its thrilling conclusion in the third and final hour of WPT’s extended coverage at the Bicycle Casino. There have been some daring plays but it’s time to see whose gamble will pay off on this rollercoaster of a final table. Tony Dunst breaks it down in The Raw Deal while Mike Sexton and Vince Van Patten bring us all the surprises in the final hands of this exhilarating competition.

programme.title: The World Poker Tour Season 11 Episode 7
programme.desc: The World Poker Tour has travelled to France for the celebrated Grand Prix de Paris and the final table is looking like a Who’s Who of international pros. Five of the finalists have won big time tournaments across the globe but right now the only amateur on the felt, Matt Salsberg, is in the chip lead. However, it won’t be an easy competition for anyone with season nine Grand Prix de Paris champion Theo Jorgensen up to make poker history by being the first to win the same WPT event twice. Kimberly Lansing anchors as Mike Sexton and Vince Van Patten call the action at the Aviation Club de France.

programme.title: The World Poker Tour Season 11 Episode 8
programme.desc: WPT’s coverage of the Grand Prix de Paris resumes at the grandiose Aviation Club de France where five players remain alive, bringing Theo Jorgensen one step closer to making poker history with a second Grand Prix de Paris title however, chip-leading Hollywood producer and so called amateur Matt Salsburg is still standing in his way, along with three gifted and aggressive international pros. Off the felt we take a look back at the best bluff from season ten while Mike Sexton and Vince Van Patten call the dynamic action on this exciting final table.

programme.title: The World Poker Tour Season 11 Episode 9
programme.desc: It’s a three way brawl in Paris when Hollywood producer, Matt Salzburg, comes up against two of the most successful poker pros of the last few years ruthless German pro Philipp Gruissem and season nine’s Grand Prix de Paris returning champ Theo Jorgensen. Commentators Mike Sexton and Vince Van Patten bring you all the twists and turns in this exciting conclusion to the first televised international title of season eleven.

programme.title: The World Poker Tour Season 11 Episode 10
programme.desc: World Poker Tour ignited the global poker boom with a unique television show based on a series of high-stakes tournaments. WPT events turned Gus Hansen into the Great Dane and Daniel Negreanu into Kid Poker, and created dozens of poker-made millionaires.

programme.title: The World Poker Tour Season 11 Episode 11
programme.desc: It’s already proved to be a rollercoaster at the final table with three players finding themselves in the chip-leading position so far and all six surviving into our second hour of coverage. Off the felt we take a look back at a war of words in one of the best moments from the historic tenth season of WPT and more detailed analysis from resident poker expert Tony Dunst in The Raw Deal. Kimberly Lansing hosts while Mike Sexton and Vince Van Patten give the sideline commentary at the renowned Borgata Poker Open.

programme.title: The World Poker Tour Season 11 Episode 12

programme.desc: While Macau is a Portuguese/Chinese mash, it's the great God of gambling that controls this island. Here, Tony plays baccarat with a local legend, kart races with a Macau champion, and dives off the world's highest bungee jump.

programme.desc: Tony roars thought the High Desert of California US in a classic Thunderbird. He meets up with local Josh Homme of Queens of The Stone Age and they explore the area while recording a soundtrack at The Rancho de la Luna studio.

programme.title: Anthony Bourdain: No Reservations - Ukraine
programme.desc: Tony and Zamir team up for a trip to the former Soviet Republic, the Ukraine. They first head to Crimea, a peninsula along the Black Sea that served as a vital strategic port for the Soviet Union. Once a top-secret hub for nuclear Soviet submersibles, the port is now a museum. Over a seaside meal of typical Zakuski cuisine, they discuss the dangers of their next destination, Chernobyl. Now a radiated ghost town, Pripayat is littered with decaying remnants of human life and will remain uninhabitable for the next 24,000 years. From here the pair carry on to celebrate Victory Day in Kiev's Independence Square. They enjoy green borscht, a staple in Ukrainian dining, beef dumplings and bacon-wrapped chicken liver. Afterwards, Zamir explores his Crimean roots when he and Tony visit Salachick in the mountain village of Bakhchisaray. Here Tony and Zamir discover traditions such as chickpea soup, bread, dolmas (stuffed grape leaves), lamb chops, and a flaky meat pie known as ciborek. After visiting Kiev's hundred-year old food market, Tony concludes his Ukrainian adventure with some American fast-food faire at McFoxy, a counterfeit McDonald-like chain.

programme.title: Anthony Bourdain: No Reservations - Kurdistan
programme.desc: Tony and his crew venture to Kurdistan, a war zone and fledgling country, to discover the tragic history and hopeful future of the ethnic group known as the Kurds. The crew begins their adventure at a hazardous environment-training course in Virginia. They are instructed on how to deal with war zones, militia, treating battle wounds and mine fields. Tony's first stop is a surprise, an amusement park known as Pank Resort. He picnics with a family eats biryani and learns how the area is rapidly developing. At a cemetery, he pays his respects to the 300,000 Kurds killed under Saddam's regime. Following, he watches a wedding that is a celebration of life. Before they leave, the crew suits up in body armor as they pass through Mosul, one of the most dangerous areas in the country. On his last day, he eats his final meal at a restaurant in Anatolia, discussing the hopes that one day soon the Kurds will have a democratic nation of their own.

programme.title: Anthony Bourdain: No Reservations - Cajun Country
programme.desc: Tony travels beyond New Orleans and into Cajun Country, to find what sets the bayou culture apart from the mainland. He dines with two famous locals, Wendell Pierce and Lolis Elie then ends his trip at an authentic crawfish boil.

programme.title: Sell This House!:Jersey City, NJ
programme.desc: Arthur and Katie are ready to retire and move on to a home in Arizona. They have had their two bedroom townhome on the market for over six months with no interest what so ever. The place is boring and very outdated. Buyers are turned off and don't even remember going through the house. Designer and staging expert Roger Hazard helps Arthur and Katie do a total home staging makeover. Roger removes over half their furniture and sends it off to storage. Painting the bland white walls with a new coat of paint along with a dark accent wall makes the place contemporary and a stand-out for buyers. Roger had our homeowners do several projects including artwork for the dining room wall. Their home sold the day after we left! And, as part of the deal, the buyers wanted Arthur and Katie's Masterpiece included.

Some rooms feel dated and stuffy with too many faux flower arrangements and antiques, while others oddly feature an English bar and Vegas-style slot machine! Ralph and Peg have run out of luck and they desperately need someone to teach them a lesson in staging. Watch as Designer Roger Hazard transforms their home into the updated living space that it should be using a few contemporary pieces of furniture and Ralph and Peg's artistic skills. Tanya Memme hosts.

programme.title: Sell This House!:Woburn, MA
programme.desc: Bill & Stephanie bought their house in Boston's suburbs with some friends, split it down the middle and set about to remodel the interior. Although there are some nice features in the home, there are some questionable color choices--giving the home no cohesive flow, some furniture design issues, and a whole lot of clutter. Stephanie's uncle is an art dealer in the area, so they have lots of interesting art, but it may be scaring away potential buyers. Now they're looking to sell their half of the duplex. Design and staging expert Roger Hazard is on the job. He sets out to add more flow to the home, designs a proper dining room, and comes up with a clever solution for oddly placed windows in the master bedroom. He also turns an upstairs storage room into a beautiful home office. Tanya Memme hosts.

programme.title: Sell This House!:Clearwater, FL

Watch as Designer Roger Hazard uses his magic to turn this house into a gorgeous beach bungalow designed to sell. Tanya Memme hosts.

programme.title: Sell This House!:West Orange, NJ
programme.desc: Wally, Laura and their son Allen, live in the bedroom community of West Orange, New Jersey, just a short commute from New York City. Homes in this hot market typically sell within a month, but so far, they've had no offers! The families looking to buy in this area are young and unfortunately the Salley house dates itself with stuffy wallpaper and lots of antique furniture and furnishings that look like they belong at Grandma's house. Staging expert Roger Hazard adds a modern touch that will appeal to buyers in the area. He transforms a dining room into a contemporary eating area, gives the feminine master bedroom a neutral makeover, and reinvents a cluttered bonus room into an inviting, important space. Tanya Memme hosts.

programme.title: Seis y Medio
programme.desc: Un hombre y una mujer debaten, se sorprenden, descubren y filosofan sobre el amor desde una novedosa posición: desde la altura de un 6,5. Es una reflexión con ironía y sin complejos que nace de una pareja surgida de los restos de dos relaciones anteriores mal terminadas y aún no olvidadas. Entre discusiones y teorías sobre la vida, se destapan infidelidades, escriben cláusulas de obligado cumplimiento, definen mil conceptos relativos al amor, se aman concentrados activamente en sus anteriores amores… Una pareja a la que, extrañamente, le cuesta disolverse. ¿Quizás porque se quieren un seis y medio?

programme.title: La Promesa
programme.desc: Cada año cientos de mujeres caen en las redes de reclutadores que trafican con personas, viéndose forzadas a una vida de esclavitud sexual y laboral. Esta es la historia de Ana, Frida y Seleni, tres bellas jóvenes, engañadas bajo la promesa de alcanzar la vida soñada. Inocentes y vulnerables, con la férrea convicción de que pese a las condiciones adversas en las que viven, pueden alcanzar un mejor futuro, serán engañadas y utilizadas por personas inescrupulosas que las adentrarán en una red de prostitución de la que no podrán escapar.

programme.title: El Turista
programme.desc: Desde el campamento base del Everest hasta el desierto australiano, a través de la Patagonia o al ritmo lento del Transmongoliano, el Turista es un programa producido y presentado por Cesar Sar, quien viaja por todo el mundo a través de un gran número de países durante más de 400 días y donde nos presenta sus aventuras, nos da consejos, comparte historias y nos enseña eventos curiosos que suceden a lo largo del camino. Catorce horas de televisión con más de 260 historias cortas que saltan de un punto a otro del planeta.

programme.title: Hermanitas Calle
programme.desc: Las hermanitas Calle son dos mujeres humildes que dan todo por su familia, por su carrera artística y por un género musical que las baña de gloria y de fama, pero les arrebata gran parte de su infancia y toda su juventud. Nelly y Fabiola Calle se aferran a sus voces y se lanzan a posicionar la música popular, un género despreciado por emisoras y disqueras. Su vida no será fácil ya que serán obligadas a ser el sustento de su familia. De pequeñas sufrirán por cuenta de su papá y de adultas, por causa de sus maridos. Vivirán historias de abandono y desamor tan dramáticas como las letras de sus canciones. Su gran mérito es que arrancando desde abajo y con todo en contra, se aferran a su amor por la música y al poder desbordante de sus dos voces para lograr lo imposible: posicionar y venderle a la sociedad un género musical con el que pocos artistas alcanzan reconocimiento.

programme.title: Byron Trimble - Diary of a Short City Boy
programme.desc: Byron Trimble has traveled around the world doing comedy for conferences, churches, retreats, clubs, schools, and corporate events. He has been featured on NBC, ABC, Living Oklahoma, and the Dan Patrick Show. His hilarious blend of music and comedy in his live shows and the following generated by his online videos have enabled him to share the stage with nationally known comedians like John Crist and Anita Renfroe. Raised in Detroit, MI, he now lives in Tulsa, OK with his beautiful wife, Hannah, and three young children. Yet, he says his greatest success might be being a pastors kid his whole life and never being arrested.

programme.title: Kristin Key - Crafty
programme.desc: Kristin Key grew up a minister’s daughter in a small town in West Texas. Much like Footloose, she was raised in a no-drinking, no-dancing, no instrumental music environment. She seemed like any other well-behaved girl… until she opened her mouth. It was obvious from the beginning that she had a quick wit and undeniable sense of humor.

programme.title: Dry Bar Comedy:Dave Nihill - Documented
programme.desc: Dave is the winner of the prestigious 43rd annual San Francisco Comedy Competition, and runner up in the Moth’s largest US Grandslam storytelling competition.

programme.title: Dry Bar Comedy:K-Von - Designer Muscles
programme.desc: Half-Persian and raised in a religious family, K-Von's comedy unites sharp cultural riffs with clean delivery. In this special he takes on political correctness, cyber bullying, and the utility of cargo pants.

programme.title: Chad Thornsberry - Junk-Cars & Valet Parking
programme.desc: Chad Thornsberry was born in St. Louis, MO. From an early age he learned his family was blessed, and blessed him with humor, quick wit, and a love of storytelling. Chad’s unique comedic perspective awards audience the opportunity to laugh at the common occurrences in everyday life. Often referred to as a great writer, his straightforward style allows audiences to laugh with him and at him as they find the humor in themselves. With reflections on growing up in a trailer park and observations as an English teacher, Chad’s satiric insights look at the pitfalls that make us human. With smart humor and a conversational style, Chad has delighted audiences from the trailer park, throughout the Midwest, and from coast to coast.

programme.title: Dry Bar Comedy:Seth Tippetts - Tall. Dark. Gigante
programme.desc: Get to know Seth from the chest down. He’s big, he’s tall, but most of all he’s hilarious. Check out this Utah-raised, clean, and semi-professional comedian today!

programme.title: James Johann - Rurally Funny
programme.desc: James' childhood upbringing was significantly influenced by country music, countless bad hair cuts, and Catholic school. In 1991, James began his stand-up career in Kansas City. Today, James is a long-time veteran of the stand-up comedy circuit, performing at clubs across the country. His self-deprecating sense of humor and high energy style come together to create a unique onstage persona. James relies more on his brain than the profane and his comedy is a truthful and hilarious reflection of life as he sees it.

programme.title: Dry Bar Comedy:Jeff Jena - Old Dog, New Jokes
programme.desc: Jeffrey Jena is one of the top corporate and cruise comics working today. His thirty-three years of live performance experience and over forty national television shows, both as an actor and comic give him the ability to work for any audience

programme.title: Dry Bar Comedy:Aaron Woodall - Sad and Needy
programme.desc: Between his first and second special, Aaron Woodalls perspective transitioned from a nice young man coming to grips with a dirty, cynical world to a deeper introspection of his own upbringing and biases.

programme.title: Dry Bar Comedy:Tom Ryan - Off The Verge
programme.desc: Over the years Tom Ryan has worked steadily at comedy clubs, concert venues, corporate functions and colleges across the U.S.. He has also made national television appearances on Showtime, A&E Comedy Central, and… Three times on “The Late Show with David Letterman!”. He has performed as the opening act in concert for: B.B. King, Tim Allen, Steven Wright, Natalie Cole, and Dennis Miller just to name a few. He has contributed monologue jokes to the award winning "Politically Incorrect with Bill Maher" and regularly headlines corporate events for companies ranging from Coca-Cola to Church and Dwight. Tom believes that the best comedy comes from the most unlikely sources.

programme.title: Tom Clark - I'm A Rescue
programme.desc: Tom Clark was born and raised, in that order. Clark’s mix of well-crafted jokes and spontaneous crowd work has led to appearances on TBS’s ‘Conan,’ CBS’s ‘Late Late Show, and Comedy Central’s ‘Premium Blend’. Clark has traveled coast to coast doing stand up and has performed internationally as part of New Faces at the prestigious‘Just For Laughs Comedy Festival’ in Montreal and on The Main Stage at ‘The Capetown Comedy Festival’ in South Africa. Clark is also an actor and has appeared on such shows as NBC’s ‘Outsourced’, TNT’s ‘The Closer’,and the Hallmark made for TV movie ‘The Wish List’. After landing the role on ‘Outsourced,’ director Ken Kwapis invited Clark to be in the Drew Barrymore movie, ‘Big Miracle’. You can also see Clark in Columbia Pictures ‘Freaks of Nature.’

programme.title: Dry Bar Comedy:Paul Morrissey - A Real Humdinger
programme.desc: Paul was raised as a sports fanatic in the tiny town of Owego, in upstate New York. After four years of playing college basketball, somehow he graduated. Aside from playing in the NBA, his dream job was to talk about sports for a living. Paul then moved to California after landing a television sports anchor job but found out quickly that he was “too much of a smart-ass” for TV news. After he was fired, Paul took his unique sense of humor to comedy club stages all over the country. In 2005, Paul was selected to perform at the HBO Comedy Festival in Las Vegas. Morrissey has also been a finalist in several national comedy competitions including Wendy’s Comedy Challenge, Comedy Central’s Open Mic Fight and Maxim’s Real Men of Comedy.

programme.desc: Rik Roberts brings a little bit of Nashville everywhere he goes. From quick bits about family and technology, to surprising stories about marriage and music – you’ll find something you can relate to. Growing up in Kentucky, he got his hands dirty working

The Ninja dismiss him as a threat, but regret that choice after Lloyd wakes up the evil snake tribe. A prophecy is revealed that states a green ninja will ultimately defeat Lord Garmadon.

programme.title: The Book Of Monsters, Part 1 - Episode 101
programme.desc: When Jestro the Jester finds the Book of Monsters, chaos breaks loose in the Kingdom of Knighton. Can the newly graduated Knights from the Knights' Academy save the kingdom? It's final graduation fighting exams for the latest Knights from Knights' Academy. All our new Knights demonstrate their prowess: CLAY, AARON, AXL and LANCE. PRINCESS MACY get to join them, but her father doesn't want her to graduate. As part of the entertainment, MERLOK does an amazing magic trick. His act is followed by...JESTRO, the King's Jester. He's terrible (and he should know to never follow a better act.) Everyone laughed because he's a real joke....a total failure. While Jestro roams the halls fo the King's Castle, forlorn, he hears the BOOK OF MONSTERS calling to him from Merlok's library. The book talks Jestro into gathering as many books of spells as he can carry, but they're interrupted by...Clay! As Jestro quickly pages through the Book of Monsters to attack Clay, Merlok arrives. There's a battle in the library between Jestro and Merlok. Finally, the wizard summons up his most powerful spell in self-defence. BOOM! There's a big, magical explosion and when Clay forces his way back into the library, Merlok, Jestro and the magic books are...GONE!

programme.title: New Girl In Town - Episode 1
programme.desc: When the World Petacular comes to Heartlake City and is almost ruined before it's even started, five feisty girls unite, despite their differences, using their creativity to save the day. Best friends Olivia, Andrea, Emma, Mia and Stephanie reside in HeartLake City but didn't know each other - that is until the World Petacular brought them together! On the eve of the biggest event Heartlake City hosts, disaster and chaos is abound. New-in-town Olivia is helping her veterinarian Aunt Sophie with her mobile clinic. But when she's put in charge of training a scruffy puppy named Scarlet, the puppy runs amuck, leaving a trail of destruction as she collides with Andrea, ruins Emma's banner and Stephanie's cakes, and finally spooks Mia's horse Bella who bucks Mia off and sprints away. The girls quickly unite, helping each-other to save the day and most importantly have fun along the way!

programme.title: Home
programme.desc: Back in training mode with the looming threat of Lloyd and the Hypnobrai, Zane wanders after a Falcon and lands himself in a heap of trouble. The rest of the Ninja leave the training dojo to help him and return to find that the snakes have burned it to the ground.

programme.title: The Book Of Monsters, Part 2 - Episode 102
programme.desc: Realizing they must defend the Kingdom from Jestro's monsters, the Knights try to organize but are despondent when they discover their best advisor - Merlok the Magician - has sacrificed himself to save them. When Jestro awakens, he's been blasted miles and miles away from the King's Castle by Merlok's explosive spell. And, it seems, all the books he was trying to steal have been scattered, too. The Book of Monsters broke Jestro' fall and now he can use the book to attack the people who laughed at him. Meanwhile, the King and his newly-trained Knights pick through the rubble of Merlok's library. They'll have to figure something out, because Jestro and his newly made magic monsters attack King's Castle! Clay organizes the Knights to defend the kingdom, but they've never worked together before. It takes all their training, plus the help of an old friend...MERLOK! Only now he's MERLOK 2.0. Ava has been piecing together what happened and discovering that the "ghost in the machine" she's been chasing is really Merlok in digital form. Now, he can use his magic digitally and he downloads just the right weapons to the struggling Knights! They finally foil Jestro's attack with Merlok's help and officially become NEXO KNIGHTS!

programme.title: Stephanie's Surprise Party -Episode 2
programme.desc: When Emma, Olivia, Andrea and Mia plan a surprise party for Stephanie's birthday, they soon discover that it's not easy keeping their plans secret from Stephanie who becomes suspicious when none of the girls have time to hang out. When Emma, Olivia, Andrea and Mia plan a surprise party for Stephanie's birthday, they discover that it's not easy keeping their plans a secret. As the girls choreograph a dance routine, magic show and search for the perfect present and cake, Stephanie becomes aware that her friends are avoiding her on her birthday and excluding her from their activities... Little does she know that her friends are secretly preparing a surprise pool party for her! Once the surprise is revealed Stephanie realises how much her friends care about her and the importance of friendship.

programme.title: Snakebit
programme.desc: Lloyd, having been kicked out of the Hynobrai snake tribe unlocks a second tribe - The Fangpyres - to help him regain control. The Ninja are busy setting up their new HQ that Zane discovered, but are called to duty when the Fangpyres attack the village where Jay's family lives.

programme.title: The Power Of Merlok - Episode 103
programme.desc: When Jestro attacks a village on the far side of the Kingdom, the NEXO-Knights wonder how they'll get there. Then Macy remembers her dad has a royal RV...maybe they can "mod" that for their own, "knightly" use? Now the NEXO-Knights get rolling...in THE FORTREX, their own ROLLING CASTLE! This great new HQ, which houses Merlok 2.0 as an operating system, will be how the knights move around Knighton and protect it from Jestro and his monsters. Speaking of the evil jester, in this episode Jestro uses some newly-made monsters to attack a town far from the capitol where he thinks he's safe from the Knights' reach. We see two parallel stories here: the Knights training, learning more about digital magic and getting organized as a team and at the same time we see Jestro making monsters, trying to learn how his powers work and talking to the Book. In the end, the Knights roll up in their castle and defeat Jestro and his marauding monsters. Lance thinks he should be the leader because he's a snot. "Of course I'm the leader...I'm a Richmond."

The girls learn that they have to compromise and trust in each other if they are to save the dolphins and their trip out to sea...

The Book of Monsters actually tells Jestro NOT to feed it to him he tells Jestro he's not ready for that kind of power. But Jestro doesn't listen. Now the Book unleashes chaotic monsters and Jestro uses them to attack the King and his party who are on a business-related tour of the kingdom. When the NEXO-Knights show up to stop the monster attacks and realize that they must save King and Queen Halbert - Macy's parents - from the chaotic evil monsters that have been unleashed. Clay asserts himself as leader and brings order to the knights from the chaos. He has his own book: the Book of the Knight's Code. They should all live by it.

Mia invites her friends to her grandparents' ranch for the weekend. But when Olivia accidentally knocks down a neighbor's barn with a tractor, the girls promise to raise the money to rebuild it themselves. Complicating matters, Mia and Stephanie turn out to like the same boy, Martin. They'll have to learn to set aside their differences and work together if they're going to raise enough money to make good on their promise.

But he feeds it to the book of Book of Monsters, and he uses it to call forth WHIPPERELLA, a monster that can induce fear. One-by-one she uses her "knighmarish" power on the knights and they experiences their own worst fears. Clay fears not living up to the Knights' Code. Lance fears being a nobody. Macy fears never being a knight and Axl fears having no food. Aaron must take the lead because he's fearless he does everything with reckless abandon. It's not until he leads the group out of the forest - as they fight off the Whipperella - that they we find out Aaron's true fear - the fear of peace and quiet and no more challenges or high energy escapades.
